course: main course
---

First, let's get podding! Slit each @broad bean pods{1%pod}(slit along the seam) with a #knife{} or your nails if you have long ones! Tip: Be gentle though, you don't want to cut the broad beans! Run your thumb along the furry inside to push the broad beans out.

> We're sending you whole broad beans in their jackets (pods), so that they have a little extra safety padding for their journey to your kitchen this evening – happy podding!

Cut the @red onion{1}(in half through the root, peeled and chopped into roughly ½cm pieces) and chop into roughly ½cm pieces. Cut the top and bottoms of the @courgette{2}(top and bottoms removed, cut in half lengthways, then into four long strips, then chopped into 1cm chunks) then in half lengthways, cut each half into four long strips then chop into 1cm chunks. Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{} if you have one). Pull the @mint{1}(leaves pulled off stalks and roughly chopped) leaves off their stalks and roughly chop.

Slit each @pork & oregano sausage{500%g} in half and discard the skin. Roll the sausage meat into meatballs (five per person) and leave to the side.

Put your onion in a #large frying pan{} with a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} on medium heat. Cook for ~{4%minutes} then add your courgette, a good pinch of @salt{pinch} and a good grind of @black pepper{grind}. Cook for another ~{6-7%minutes} before adding your garlic. Stir together and cook for ~{1%minute}, then pour in the @orzo{360%g}. Stir until your orzo is well coated in the garlicky oil, then pour in the @water{800%ml} and the @vegetable stock pot{1}.

Bring to the boil, stirring to dissolve your stock pot, then turn the heat down to low and simmer away (don't let it boil rapidly!), for ~{10%minutes}, or until your orzo is 'al dente' and the liquid has been absorbed.

> 'Al dente' simply means the pasta is cooked through but has a tiny bit of firmness left in the middle. Stir every couple of mins to ensure it doesn't stick to the bottom of the pan!

> If all the liquid has been absorbed and the orzo is not quite cooked, just add 50ml of water and keep cooking (repeat this if you need to).

While your orzotto is cooking, add your meatballs to a #frying pan{} on medium heat with a drizzle of @oil{drizzle}. Cook for ~{8-9%minutes} until they are browned and cooked through.

> The meatballs are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Remove the pan from the heat.

When your orzotto is 4 mins from being ready, add your broad beans to the pan to cook for the last ~{4%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat. Crumble the @feta cheese{1}(crumbled) into the pan along with your mint and stir together. Taste and add some salt and pepper if you feel it needs it.

Squeeze some @lemon{1}(juice squeezed) juice into a #bowl{} with a drizzle of @oil{drizzle}, a @salt{pinch} and a good grind of @black pepper{grind}. Add the @peashoots{2%Steve's Leaves}(do not use) to the bowl and toss together.

Serve your orzotto in #bowls{} with your meatballs and pea shoots on top. Enjoy!